steps.instruction:
- Microwave pancakes 1 minutes on high up until they are thawed
- Cut them in half
- Coat a 9 inch square baking dish with spray oil
- Arrange in 2 rows, overlapping pancakes shingle with the cut edge down
- Place half & half and sugar in medium saucepan
- Heat  on medium for 2 to 3 minutes or until steaming
- Remove pan from heat
- Beat all the eggs
- Whisk eggs and vanilla into the hot mixture for 30 seconds
- Preheat oven to 325F
- Pour egg mixture over pancakes
- Let stand for 15 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed
- Top with blueberries
- Bake for 20 to 25 minutes
- Top pancakes with granola, bake for 4 to 5 more minutes
- Let stand for 5 minutes
- Serve with maple syrup
